_at": "2017-04-15T05:58:44Z", "closed_at": "2017-04-15T05:58:44Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Non-exhaustive list of possible candidates:\n- operating system (i.e. `/dev/urandom` or `GenCryptRandom`)\n- [eSTREAM family](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ESTREAM)\n- [ChaCha family](http://cr.yp.to/chacha.html)\n- [Salsa20](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salsa20)\n\nImportant considerations:\n- performance\n- statistical/cryptographic strength\n- how far into the realm of cryptography do we want to go? (Not very far, but implementing an PRNG isn't as hard to get correct/test as other areas of cryptography, since (a) its output can be compared byte-for-byte with a known-correct implementation and (b) RNGs (for the most part) lacks some subtle constraints like constant time equality and other side channel attacks that other cryptographic algorithms require.)\n\nThe [ISAAC Rng](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISAAC_%28cipher%29) currently implemented in `std::rand` has some known weaknesses, but is generally accepted as cryptographically secure (although it has not received a huge amount of scrutiny).\n", "closed_by": {"login": "aturon", "id": 709807, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjcwOTgwNw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/709807?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon", "html_url": "https://github.com/aturon", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.